{"article_id":"o3uOmk5vIDyooMFK","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The House on Friday dealt a staggering blow to President Barack Obama ' s trade agenda ,","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"as Democrats turned en masse against the president","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"just hours after he made a direct appeal","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"to salvage a centerpiece of his second-term platform .","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"Lawmakers easily defeated a measure","depth":9},{"id":5,"text":"to help workers","depth":10},{"id":6,"text":"displaced by free trade","depth":10},{"id":7,"text":"known as Trade Adjustment Assistance .","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"The aid package needed to pass","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"in order to enact companion legislation","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"that would give Obama fast-track trade authority","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"to complete the sweeping , 12-nation Trans-Pacific Partnership trade pact .","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"\" Whatever the deal is with other countries , \"","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"Minority Leader Nancy Pelosi","depth":11},{"id":14,"text":"( D-Calif. )","depth":11},{"id":15,"text":"said before the vote ,","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"breaking her longtime silence on the issue ,","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"\" we want a better deal for America ' s workers . \"","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"The vote came","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"after President Barack Obama , in a last-ditch effort , made a rare visit to the Capitol","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"to lobby for legislation .","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"He implored Democrats to \" play it straight \" on the decisive vote .","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"Obama spent roughly 40 minutes with Democratic lawmakers ,","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"taking no questions","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"but telling his party to \" vote your values , \"","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"according to a source in the room .","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"But Democratic lawmakers rebuffed him hours later ,","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"voting overwhelmingly","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"to scuttle the trade package","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"that was a centerpiece of the president ' s second-term agenda .","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"Minority Leader Nancy Pelosi","depth":12},{"id":31,"text":"( D-Calif. ) ,","depth":12},{"id":32,"text":"who had remained silent for weeks on the trade issue ,","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"went to the House floor shortly before the vote","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"to speak against the trade deal .","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"Afterward , Pelosi linked trade to her party ' s uphill effort","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"to enact a long-term highway funding bill .","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"\" The prospects for passage of \" the trade bill ,","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"she wrote in a letter to fellow Democrats ,","depth":11},{"id":39,"text":"\" will greatly increase with the passage of a robust highway bill . \"","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"After TAA failed ,","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"the House approved fast-track legislation ,","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"known as Trade Promotion Authority ,","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"in a 219-211 vote .","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"But that vote was largely for show ,","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"because enactment of TPA is contingent on approval of TAA .","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"The House could vote again on TAA next week .","depth":7},{"id":47,"text":"If enough votes flipped","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"to pass it ,","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"it would mean that TPA prevailed as well ,","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"because the two bills are interconnected .","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"House Republican leaders say","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"they have 100 votes for TAA ,","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"and Democrats would need to provide 118","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"if another vote happens .","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"On Friday , Democrats provided 40 votes for TAA ,","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"while 86 Republicans supported it .","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"In other words , Democrats would need to essentially triple their vote total","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"to pass the measure .","depth":8},{"id":59,"text":"White House spokesman Josh Earnest downplayed the defeat as a \" procedural snafu , \"","depth":6},{"id":60,"text":"comparing it to the Senate ' s initial rejection of the legislation","depth":7},{"id":61,"text":"before it was later adopted .","depth":7},{"id":62,"text":"\" To the surprise of very few , another procedural snafu has emerged , ' '","depth":7},{"id":63,"text":"Earnest told reporters .","depth":7},{"id":64,"text":"\" These kinds of entanglements are endemic to the House of Representatives . ' '","depth":6},{"id":65,"text":"With his trade push on the ropes ,","depth":7},{"id":66,"text":"Obama headed to Capitol Hill Friday morning","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"to plead with his party to bail him out .","depth":8},{"id":68,"text":"The president needed to convince Democrats to back TAA ,","depth":8},{"id":69,"text":"which would provide aid and retraining to workers","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"who lose their jobs to trade agreements .","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"The TAA bill was intertwined with legislation","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"to give Obama Trade Promotion Authority .","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"House Democrats","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"- most of whom have been firmly entrenched in their position for weeks -","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"emerged from the meeting with the president still divided .","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"Rep. Earl Blumenauer , a pro-trade Democrat from Oregon , said","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"Obama \" hit it out of the park . \"","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"\" It was a powerful presentation , \"","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"Blumeuaer said .","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"But another supporter , Rep. Gerry Connolly","depth":12},{"id":81,"text":"( D-Va. )","depth":12},{"id":82,"text":"said afterward","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"it would be an \" uphill climb","depth":11},{"id":84,"text":"to get to 217 , \"","depth":11},{"id":85,"text":"referring to the number of votes","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"needed","depth":11},{"id":87,"text":"to pass a bill .","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"\" TAA has always been an absolute admission to me","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"that there is going to be lots of lost jobs , \"","depth":9},{"id":90,"text":"Rep. Louise Slaughter , a top House Democrat from New York , said before the vote .","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"Multiple Democrats echoed that sentiment on the House floor .","depth":7},{"id":92,"text":"There was also palpable anger at the president","depth":6},{"id":93,"text":"leading up to the vote .","depth":6},{"id":94,"text":"Rep. Peter DeFazio said","depth":7},{"id":95,"text":"he thought","depth":8},{"id":96,"text":"Obama \" tried to guilt people","depth":9},{"id":97,"text":"and impugn their integrity . \"","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"\" There was a number of us","depth":8},{"id":99,"text":"who were insulted , \"","depth":8},{"id":100,"text":"DeFazio","depth":9},{"id":101,"text":"( D-Ore. )","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"said in an interview after the meeting with Obama .","depth":8},{"id":103,"text":"Obama acknowledged the uncertainty","depth":7},{"id":104,"text":"surrounding the Friday vote ,","depth":7},{"id":105,"text":"which turned out to be much more lopsided","depth":7},{"id":106,"text":"than anyone expected .","depth":7},{"id":107,"text":"\" I don ' t think","depth":8},{"id":108,"text":"you ever nail anything down around here ,","depth":8},{"id":109,"text":"it ' s always moving , \"","depth":7},{"id":110,"text":"the president told reporters","depth":7},{"id":111,"text":"after he spoke with lawmakers .","depth":7},{"id":112,"text":"Republicans and Democrats were predicting ahead of the vote","depth":6},{"id":113,"text":"that TAA was headed for defeat","depth":7},{"id":114,"text":"- bringing fast track down with it -","depth":7},{"id":115,"text":"unless the dynamic dramatically shifted this morning .","depth":5},{"id":116,"text":"Obama ' s visit to Capitol Hill , a rare round of personal lobbying by a president","depth":5},{"id":117,"text":"not known for his relationships with lawmakers ,","depth":5},{"id":118,"text":"was designed to do just that .","depth":4},{"id":119,"text":"Obama arrived at Pelosi ' s second-floor Capitol office suite at 9:41 a.m. ,","depth":5},{"id":120,"text":"waving to a small group of reporters","depth":6},{"id":121,"text":"gathered in the hallway .","depth":6},{"id":122,"text":"He walked into the House Democratic Caucus meeting with Pelosi and Rep. Jim Clyburn","depth":6},{"id":123,"text":"( D-S.C. ) ,","depth":6},{"id":124,"text":"the assistant minority leader .","depth":5},{"id":125,"text":"Obama also made an appearance at the congressional baseball game on Thursday night ,","depth":6},{"id":126,"text":"and top administration officials","depth":8},{"id":127,"text":"- including Labor Secretary Thomas Perez , Treasury Secretary Jack Lew , and White House Chief of Staff Denis McDonough -","depth":8},{"id":128,"text":"have been meeting with Democrats for the past several days .","depth":7},{"id":129,"text":"Some Democrats were clearly unmoved by the direct appeal from the commander-in-chief .","depth":6},{"id":130,"text":"\" We ' re going to win today , \"","depth":8},{"id":131,"text":"Rep. Bill Pascrell","depth":10},{"id":132,"text":"( D-N.J. ) ,","depth":10},{"id":133,"text":"a member of the Ways and Means Committee , declared before the meeting with Obama .","depth":9},{"id":134,"text":"\" No on both . \"","depth":7},{"id":135,"text":"The eleventh hour drama came","depth":5},{"id":136,"text":"as top lawmakers and aides said","depth":6},{"id":137,"text":"they had no idea going in how Friday ' s momentous vote would play out .","depth":6},{"id":138,"text":"Pelosi","depth":8},{"id":139,"text":"( D-Calif. )","depth":8},{"id":140,"text":"had been mum on both bills bill ,","depth":7},{"id":141,"text":"which created an opening","depth":7},{"id":142,"text":"for liberal opposition to TAA to swell .","depth":7},{"id":143,"text":"House Minority Whip Steny Hoyer","depth":10},{"id":144,"text":"( D-Md . )","depth":10},{"id":145,"text":"said","depth":9},{"id":146,"text":"he planned to vote for TAA ,","depth":9},{"id":147,"text":"but didn ' t signal his position on the larger fast-track bill .","depth":9},{"id":148,"text":"Rep. Jim Clyburn","depth":9},{"id":149,"text":"( D-S.C. ) ,","depth":9},{"id":150,"text":"the assistant Democratic leader , was undecided .","depth":8},{"id":151,"text":"House Republican leaders needed a large number of Democrats","depth":9},{"id":152,"text":"to vote for TAA","depth":9},{"id":153,"text":"in order for it to pass .","depth":8},{"id":154,"text":"\" I think","depth":11},{"id":155,"text":"Republicans are going to provide a share of their votes","depth":12},{"id":156,"text":"based upon what Republicans have done in the past ,","depth":12},{"id":157,"text":"and it ' s up to the Democrat leadership and the president to get Democrats on board , \"","depth":10},{"id":158,"text":"Rep. Pat Tiberi","depth":11},{"id":159,"text":"( R-Ohio )","depth":11},{"id":160,"text":"said on Thursday .","depth":10},{"id":161,"text":"He , along with House Ways and Means Committee Chairman Paul Ryan","depth":10},{"id":162,"text":"( R-Wis. ) ,","depth":10},{"id":163,"text":"led the pro-trade whip operation .","depth":9},{"id":164,"text":"Democrats have traditionally backed TAA , with its focus","depth":8},{"id":165,"text":"on helping struggling unemployed workers .","depth":8},{"id":166,"text":"But Democrats complained to White House officials this week","depth":9},{"id":167,"text":"that the TAA package was too small ,","depth":9},{"id":168,"text":"and argued","depth":9},{"id":169,"text":"the president should be leaning on Republicans","depth":10},{"id":170,"text":"to enlarge it .","depth":10},{"id":171,"text":"But many Democrats came to view the jobs assistance bill as a way","depth":7},{"id":172,"text":"to sink the entire trade package .","depth":7},{"id":173,"text":"Reps. Rosa DeLauro","depth":9},{"id":174,"text":"( D-Conn. )","depth":9},{"id":175,"text":"and Sandy Levin","depth":11},{"id":176,"text":"( Mich. ) ,","depth":11},{"id":177,"text":"the top Democrat on the Ways and Means Committee , led the push","depth":10},{"id":178,"text":"for Democrats to vote against TAA .","depth":9},{"id":179,"text":"And they were joined , in the end , by Pelosi .","depth":7},{"id":180,"text":"Defeating the jobs aid bill ,","depth":8},{"id":181,"text":"the Democratic leader said minutes before the vote ,","depth":8},{"id":182,"text":"\" is the only way","depth":8},{"id":183,"text":"we will be able to slow down fast track . \"","depth":8}],"relations":[{"parent":367,"left":299,"right":366,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":299,"left":248,"right":298,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":248,"left":223,"right":247,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":223,"left":187,"right":222,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":187,"left":0,"right":186,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":186,"left":1,"right":185,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":185,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":222,"left":200,"right":221,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":200,"left":194,"right":199,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":194,"left":190,"right":193,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":190,"left":189,"right":7,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":189,"left":4,"right":188,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":188,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":193,"left":8,"right":192,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":192,"left":9,"right":191,"relation":"elaboration","nucle